c. Placentiam (Piacenza) .· on the south bank of the Po, just below the influx of the Trebia. This is the earliest mention of the existence of the town.

d. Cremona .· on the north bank of the Po, a little below the confluence of the Addua—the sister city to Placentia. Neither it nor Placentia were taken by Hannibal.

e. colonias .· one of the main objects of a Roman colony was to keep the conquered people in check. The colonists had all the rights of Roman citizens.
